1 26.1 - 08.1 - 02. Cessation of operations .
2 1. The association shall cease enrollment under the plan effective May 1, 2025 .
3 2. After taking all reasonable steps, including those specified in this section, to timely and
4 efficiently assist in the transition of individuals receiving benefits under chapter
5 26.1 - 08, and paying health insurance claims for plan coverage and meeting all other
6 obligations of the board under this section, the association shall cease operating the
7 pool.
8 3. The association may take any action it deems necessary to:
9 a. Cease enrollment for plan coverage effective May 1, 2025 .
10 b. Terminate all existing benefit plans effective December 31, 2025 .
11 c. Provide at least a ninety-day notice to current policyholders of the termination.
12 4. This section does not require the board to revise plan benefits to comply with this
13 chapter.
14 26.1 - 08.1 - 03. Board of directors .
15 Notwithstanding any other provision of this chapter, to facilitate an efficient cessation of
16 operations, the board:
17 1. May continue to use the lead carrier to fulfill administrative tasks and operations.
18 2. Shall continue to follow the requirements of participating members under section
19 26.1 - 08 - 09 .
20 3. May implement a process to assess members based on actual program costs rather
21 than projected program costs.
22 4. Shall return any excess funds that remain after operations of the association cease to
23 the insurance regulatory trust fund.
24 26.1 - 08.1 - 04. Enrollment of individuals losing creditable coverage .
25 An individual losing creditable coverage must be provided enrollment into a comparable:
26 1. Health benefit plan; or
27 2. Plan under a Medicare supplement policy that has a benefit package classified as
28 plan A, B, C, F (including F with a high deductible), G, K, or L under guaranteed issue .
29 26.1 - 08.1 - 05. Statute of limitations .
30 A cause of action against the association or the board must be commenced within the
31 earlier of one year after the cause of action occurs or December 31, 2027 .
